description_en:
The objective of this project is for Corey Nutrition Company Inc. to get registered in order to export its products in China by completing the following three steps: 
1) obtain an import registration license from the Ministry of Agriculture, 
2) apply for market access with the General Administration of China Customs (GACC) and 
3) have their manufacturing facility be registered by GACC.
expected_results_en: To obtain the necessary authorizations to export to China.
additional_information_en: The amendment provides additional funds to cover the costs of a test required by China’s Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs.

prog_purpose_en: The AgriRisk Initiatives (ARI) program supports the development of new risk management tools for use in the agriculture sector.
agreement_title_en: The Economics and future of Margin Insurance in Canada
description_en: The objective of this project is to measure farmers response to agricultural insurance programs including crop insurance and net margin insurance; how crop insurance and net margin insurance affect productivity and welfare; and, analyze the expansion of margin insurance through public delivery and public-private partnerships.
expected_results_en: Support for academic research proposals that address issues relevant to business risk management in the Canadian agriculture sector.

prog_purpose_en: The AgriRisk Initiatives (ARI) program supports the research and development as well as the implementation and administration of new risk management tools for use in the agriculture sector.
agreement_title_en: Developing Area-Triggered Whole-Farm Margin-based Safety Nets
description_en: The objective of this project is to develop a conceptual framework to compare the efficiency, equity and efficacy of the current AgriStability program relative to an area triggered whole-farm margin based program.
expected_results_en: Support for academic research proposals that address issues relevant to business risk management in the Canadian agriculture sector.

description_en: The objective of this project is to assess how trade policy uncertainties affect farm prices and farm margins, and evaluate the implications for business risk management programs.

agreement_title_en: Prospects for Targeted Weather-Indexed Revenue Insurance for Grape and Berry Growers in British Columbia
description_en: The objective of this project is to determine if weather-index insurance (WII) be effective in mitigating the adverse impacts of weather risk on the yield and the quality of output, while simplifying and speeding up the payment process; and, to explore how can WII products complement current Canadian BRM programs to attract farmers to participate in such an insurance product.

prog_purpose_en: The Career Focus Program helps an individual acquire experience in the agricultural sector.
description_en: The objective of this project is to provide an intern with work experience.  The intern will be responsible for collecting hog farm data from clients and from internal farms; producing a batch-end report for the stages of nursery production, feeder production (with measurements of average daily gain), feed conversion and mortality rate; and producing a follow-up report on the nursery batches with measurements of the number of weaners per sow per year, the number of weaners per farrowing, the life cycle of the sow, the prolificacy of the sow, the conception rate and the culling rate, with an overview of the herd's parities.
expected_results_en: The intern will acquire career-related work experience.

prog_purpose_en: The Career Focus Program helps an individual acquire experience in the agricultural sector.
description_en: The objective of this project is to provide a work experience to an inten who will help operate a small farm on public space in North Cowichan and Duncan. This farm is managed by Cowichan Green Community’s staff . The intention is to support and increase urban agriculture production. The farm practices sustainable agriculture and landscaping based upon the principles of permaculture, offering natural pest control and sustainable water management, and alternatives to chemical fertilizers.

description_en: The objective of this project is to test the formulation and produce a bioplastic masterbatch (an additive or binder for imparting other properties to plastics), which is hypothesized to increase the biodegradability of bioplastics.
expected_results_en: Improved biodegradability of bio-based plastics derived from agricultural or wood-based biomass suitable for use as replacements for single use plastics (e.g. packaging).

description_en: This project is for the intern to gain experience as the point of contact between the Ontario farmer/grain buyer clients and an online agricultural marketplace and in leveraging the latest blockchain technology as well as writing the computer code to create an efficient, transparent and secure market
expected_results_en: The intern will acquire career-related work experience.
